            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/40383",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Could it be there is a file called smtp.php or Smtp.php in your include path? The unittests thoroughly test the behavior you describe and as such I'm not able to reproduce this issue.\r\n\r\nAwaiting more info on how to reproduce this issue.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-05-04T20:18:32.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-05-04T20:18:32.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/40384",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=afx114",
                        "name": "afx114",
                        "displayName": "jsnod",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Nope, the only smtp.php in my include path is the one in Zend\/Mail\/Transport.\r\n\r\nTo reproduce, put the following in your application.ini:\r\n\r\n{noformat}\r\nresources.mail.transport.type\t\t= smtp\r\nresources.mail.transport.host\t\t= \"smtp.server.com\"\r\nresources.mail.transport.auth\t\t= login\r\nresources.mail.transport.username\t= \"myLogin\"\r\nresources.mail.transport.password\t= \"myPasswd\"\r\n{noformat}\r\n\r\nThe above does not work.  The config below works fine:\r\n\r\n{noformat}\r\nresources.mail.transport.type\t\t= Zend_Mail_Transport_Smtp\r\nresources.mail.transport.host\t\t= \"smtp.server.com\"\r\nresources.mail.transport.auth\t\t= login\r\nresources.mail.transport.username\t= \"myLogin\"\r\nresources.mail.transport.password\t= \"myPasswd\"\r\n{noformat}\r\n\r\nI've whipped up a quick patch that works for both cases, will attach.  It's my first time submitting a patch, so please forgive me if I've done it wrong.\r\n\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=afx114",
                        "name": "afx114",
                        "displayName": "jsnod",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-05-04T20:42:08.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-05-04T20:42:08.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/40387",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The problem with your patch is that it doesn't allow for transport names like someOtherLib_Mail_Transport_SmtpFoobar. I'm closing this issue as cannot reproduce until you're able to provide a unittest, or more information on how to reproduce.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
